text.value:
Ich meine hier: 

tabIndex={isOpen ? '0' : '-1'} 

TS2322: Type string is not assignable to type number

How can I select them in my file? 

console.log(t('typewriter.1'));

withouth having to write all of them?

There are a couple ways you can select the typewriter messages without having to write them all out:

1. Use Object.values() to get an array of all the values:

```js
const typewriterMessages = Object.values(t('typewriter'));

console.log(typewriterMessages[0]); 
```

2. Get a random message:

```js 
const keys = Object.keys(t('typewriter'));
const randomKey = keys[Math.floor(Math.random() * keys.length)];

console.log(t(`typewriter.${randomKey}`));
```

3. Loop through the keys:

```js
const typewriter = t('typewriter'); 

for (let key in typewriter) {
  console.log(typewriter[key]);
}
```

So in your code, you could do something like:

```js
const message = t('typewriter')[Math.floor(Math.random() * 12) + 1];

console.log(message);
```

This will randomly pick one of the 12 messages each time.

Let me know if this helps or if you need any clarification!
